race.comment: XCESSIVE FORCE (8) stands out pitted against moderate opposition. Just missed ina CL2 at Randwick before the spell and resumed with a big win over this distance in a CL4 at Goulburn. Was backed off the map and draws low today. Proven second-up and carrying 3kg less should have them well covered. MOSGOLD (3) won an 82 at Parkes leading all the way. Has the early speed to clear the wide barrier and will be in the money if that's achieved economically. KEIKOKU (7) just missed here two back this grade and was slow off at the track following. He's been freshened and is a trifecta chance if he can avoid being bottled up from an inside gate. CRAVING MAGIC (15) was beaten less than 2L in a Showcase sprint at Moroya just five days ago. Must be pleasing and Collett will give him every chance from an inside barrier.
